data.name: Label5.Text
data.value:
1. Go to the "Employee" Tab and fillout the important details about your employee. After you fillout the details, click Next button to direct you to another tab.
2. You're in the "Work Information" Tab. Select one of the options to your employee such as his/her Restdays in a week, Work Status and his/her Government ID. After you fillout the details, then click Continue button.
3. Now you're in the Salary Rate tab. You will need to input important details on how his payroll will be computed such as his days worked, regular rate per day, overtime rate etc. You will also need to fillout the deductions such as SSS,PHILHEALTH Etc.
4. Now the message will pop up saying "Are you sure you want to save info?" just click yes and congratulations you just complety added employee data into the database

data.name: Label7.Text
data.value:
1. Go to the "View" Tab and then search by his ID, Lastname or Firstname then click "Search" button.
2. The data of the employees will be shown in the datagrid and just click Delete button and you're done you successfully.

data.name: Label9.Text
data.value:
1. Go to the "View" Tab and click the Update button.
2. After that, Another window will pop up and just search your employee ID you want to update.
3. Select the textbox you want to update and then after that just click Update button and you're finished.

data.name: Label11.Text
data.value:
1. Go to the "Salary" Tab and then search the ID of your employee you want to compute and then click Find button.
2. The data of your employee will be showed after you search by his/her ID.
3. After the data being shown, just input his total days of worked, days absent, overtime hours and also his deductions on his salary and then click Compute button.
4. Now you will see the summary of his payroll. After that just click Save "button". You can also print his payslips.
5. Done.
